snippet.textDisplay: To the family of Kobe Bryant this is a major tragedy within your lives. The many comments, shared through caring words and the continuous of support and the love express through prayers. When you lose someone a part of you is lossed forever with them... the death of our loved ones, has left so many memories, but then again, all we have is memories of each other, past or present... How, When, Where and Why, we wonder and ask... how to deal with the devastion and pain, take the steps each day... talk to your love ones in Spirit. I've lost my entire family to tragedy and I know what it's like to be alone. Every day you learn to just be... Writing helps me, I wrote this for my daughter Lauren: Through the painful journey, the reality of your life, left me with too many questions and so few answers. Love and Peace to the Bryant family and to everyone. Take care...

"It is appointed once a man (mankind) to die...after this is judgement.

For whosoever shall call upon the name of the Lord shall be saved.

"The Lord is not slack concerning his promise, as some men count slackness; but is longsuffering to us-ward, not willing that any should perish, but that all should come to repentance."

"If we confess our sins, he is faithful and just to forgive us our sins, and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness."
1 John 1:9, KJV
